        <briefdescription>
<para>Construct and register an <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1LED" kindref="compound">LED</ref> output. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>controlId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>DCS-BIOS output address (A_4E_C_* from <ref refid="A4EC__OutputIds_8h" kindref="compound">A4EC_OutputIds.h</ref>). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Bitmask: (value &amp; mask) != 0 → on; == 0 → off. Use A_4E_C_*_AM constants, or 0xFFFF for whole-word outputs. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pin</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>GPIO or MCP23017 <ref refid="classPinRef" kindref="compound">PinRef</ref> for the <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1LED" kindref="compound">LED</ref> pin. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>reverse</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>false (default): pin HIGH = on (current-source wiring). true: pin LOW = on (current-sink, anode to VCC). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
